The paper deals with the problem of releasing individual-level data while preserving privacy, which is a common concern in the field of database systems (cs.DB) and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also introduces a new algorithm that involves solving linear equations, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the algorithm through simulation and case studies, which is a common approach in the field of data science (cs.DS).
